The paper discusses machine lipreading, which involves computer vision and audio recognition systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses challenges in knowledge sharing and scoring results, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) respectively. The paper also mentions the use of accuracy and correctness to measure system performance, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
